✅ What is Next.js and how is it different from React?
🔹 What is React?
React is a JavaScript library developed by Facebook for building user interfaces, mainly single‑page applications (SPAs).
	• Focuses only on the UI layer
	• Uses client‑side rendering (CSR) by default
	• You need to choose and configure extra tools for: 
		○ Routing (React Router)
		○ Server‑side rendering
		○ SEO
		○ Build and optimization
👉 React answers: “How do I build UI components?”

🔹 What is Next.js?
Next.js is a full‑featured framework built on top of React, developed by Vercel.
	• Uses React plus additional capabilities out of the box
	• Supports multiple rendering methods
	• Production‑ready with minimal configuration
👉 Next.js answers: “How do I build, render, optimize, and deploy a React app?”

🔍 Key Differences Between Next.js and React
Aspect	React	Next.js
Type	UI Library	React Framework
Rendering	Client‑Side Rendering (CSR)	SSR, SSG, ISR, CSR
Routing	Manual (React Router)	File‑based routing
SEO	Weak by default	SEO‑friendly
Performance	Depends on setup	Optimized by default
Backend	Needs separate backend	Built‑in API routes
Setup	More configuration	Minimal configuration
Production readiness	Developer‑driven	Enterprise‑ready

🚀 Rendering Capability Comparison
	• React
		○ Renders mostly on the browser
		○ Slower first page load
		○ SEO limitations
	• Next.js
		○ SSR (Server‑Side Rendering) → Faster first load, better SEO
		○ SSG (Static Site Generation) → Very fast pages
		○ ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration) → Best for dynamic but scalable pages

🧠 Simple Interview Answer (Client‑Round Ready)
	React is a library focused on building UI components, while Next.js is a framework built on top of React that provides routing, server‑side rendering, SEO optimization, and backend capabilities out of the box.
	In real projects, we use Next.js when performance, SEO, and scalability are important.

✅ When to Use What?
	• ✅ Use React if:
		○ You are building simple dashboards
		○ SEO is not critical
		○ You want full control over architecture
	• ✅ Use Next.js if:
		○ SEO and performance matter
		○ You need SSR/SSG
		○ You want faster development with best practices built‑in

